The 40-year-old rapper via micro blogging platform, Twitter, noted that he is speaking from a standpoint of experience. According to MI, he had experimented with being humble in Nigeria for more than a decade and at the end, he realised that it is not worth it. He then advised others seeking to follow similar path of humility to desists and walk with pride. ”Having experimented with Humility for over a decade within these shores I am here to report my findings. *clears throat* “E no de work for here. Carry your shoulder hop!” he tweeted. This article was originally published on Naija News Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!